segments.text: Piranhas are attracted to blood.

segments.text: Number two, avoid areas with netted fish, docks where fish are cleaned, and areas around bird rookeries.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Piranhas may become habituated to feeding in these areas and may be more aggressive there.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Number three,

segments.text: Stay out of the water when piranhas are feeding.

segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: If you see them feeding, stay away or well upriver.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Cross the river at night.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Virtually every species of piranha rests at night, and when awakened they will swim away rather than attack.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Piranhas are more active at dawn.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Some large adults may hunt in the evening.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Swim or walk across quickly and quietly.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Do not try to create a large disturbance in the water that might awaken piranhas.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: Be aware.

segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: and slow-moving rivers, backwaters, or floodplain lakes.

segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: The water is too cold and flows too fast.
